# The Day I Embraced Death

As a kid, I really am afraid of death. I then grow up and learn how messed up the world is. I wanted to disappear from this bloody world but then realized that death is not what I really want- it is being noticed and loved. Until one day, I experienced the best thing that I could ever experience, a kind of happiness that I never felt before. That moment was the moment I embraced death. I was so happy that time that I could actually die without having any remorse, guilt or regrets. I started to seize every moments knowing the uncertainty of death

# Incompleteness

Ever had the feeling of not being able to end up what you wanted your works to be. Like the blind, I lost my sight. Like a mute, I cannot speak. As an artist, my hands don’t work anymore. I force my piece to be something I visioned it to be but it seems to be going nowhere. My hands are already disabled. And all that’s left are the frustrations, disappointments and annoyance of not achieving what I want. Just like my canvas, I will always be incomplete. My piece will always be unending.

# 
Life in the Time of Corona (Day)

This creation is a tribute to healthcare workers in the COVID-19 pandemic, they're working endlessly, even at night, to protect and save everyone. The paper cranes hung on the wall is a symbol of peace, love, healing & hope during challenging times. It's often given to a person who's seriously ill, to wish for their recovery. I chose yellow for the paper cranes, as yellow symbolizes hope, happiness, positivity, encouragement, and energy. A reminder for everyone to stay positive in the midst of pandemic.

#  Intimacy+
The Artwork is an exploration of intimacy. Each detail represents the invisible connections made and sustained by intimacy.

It takes intimacy to really know the finer details of a person. Just like this artwork if you look at it in a single perspective you will not see the metallic line details. Those lines are a depiction of a story, or facets of a person… If we try to look closer, dig deeper. That is the time we will appreciate the person/artwork more.

#  Radiant Mystery
she is a woman of strength and mighty valor!
She’s full of wealth and wisdom.
The price paid for her was greater than many jewels.

She wraps herself in strength, might, and power in all her works.

She is known by her extravagant generosity to the poor,
for she always reaches out her hands to those in need.
